Fully static Linux binaries require the silt-static opam switch (ocaml-variants.5.3.0+options with ocaml-option-musl and ocaml-option-static). GCC 14's libgcc_eh.a references _dl_find_object (glibc-only). The weak stub in ffi/musl_compat.c provides a fallback. The .o must be linked via -cclib in bin/dune and test/dune link_flags, not just compiled into the library archive, because the linker processes archives left-to-right.